episodes.title: Inside the Internet’s Wildest Alien Cults
episodes.description:
I Found the Internet’s Strangest Alien Rabbit Hole
I thought I was just watching some fake UFO videos. Instead, I ended up in one of the weirdest corners of the internet that i didn't even know existed, people who believe they’re literal aliens, TikTok psychics scamming their viewers live, and a guy who thinks he’s channeling an interdimensional alien being named Bashar.

This is a commentary-style deep dive into internet cults, fringe beliefs, and rabbit holes that probably shouldn't exist - but somehow do. It’s the kind of video you’d expect to find next to Kurtis Conner or Oompaville. If you’ve ever gone too deep on Reddit, or watched a TikTok that made you question reality, this one’s for you.

TikTok conspiracy, reaction commentary, iceberg style topics, weird side of YouTube, internet rabbit holes, Remote viewing, internet mysteries.
